Police are investigating the cause of the accident involving two trucks, a bakkie, two minibus taxis and five other cars on the N3 South in Pietermaritzburg. Shawn Herbst from Netcare 911 has more details. #DStv403  PIETERMARITZBURG -Â A horror crash has been reported on the N3 South in Pietermaritzburg. Dozens of people have reportedly died. Two minibus taxis, two trucks, a bakkie and five cars were involved in the crash. A secondary crash took place on the N3 North while emergency services were on the scene. Police are investigating the cause of the accident.